description: Monitor seat usage and the activity of users in your Zero Trust organization.
description_user_registry_identity: Gateway uses this identity when doing policy checks. This is the last-seen identity that is stored in the User Registry.
description_user_session_identity: Session identities are the identities stored from the login event.
empty_state_description: Users will be listed here once they initiate a session with Zero Trust.
empty_state_documentation_text: In the meantime, here’s our {link} about Users.
remove_multiple_users_description_with_w:
End the users’ active session and remove them from the user registry.

This will mark the user as Inactive, and they will no longer occupy a seat unless they re-authenticate. To disable a user's ability to authenticate, modify your Access and device enrollment policies.
remove_session_failure: Error removing user sessions and devices.
remove_session_success: Successfully removed user sessions and devices.
remove_user_description:
End the user's active session and remove them from the user registry.

This will mark the user as Inactive, and they will no longer occupy a seat unless they re-authenticate. To disable a user's ability to authenticate, modify your Access and device enrollment policies.
remove_user_description_with_warning:
End the users' active session and mark them as inactive.

They will no longer occupy a seat unless they re-authenticate. To disable a user's ability to authenticate, modify your Access and device enrollment policies.
revoke_multiple_users_description:
End the users’ active session across all applications.

Revoking a session does not remove a user's seat or prevent them from logging in again. To permanently revoke a user's access, disable their account in your identity provider.
revoke_session_failure: Error revoking user session and devices.
revoke_session_success: Successfully revoked user sessions and devices.
revoke_user_description:
End the user's active session across all applications.

Revoking a session does not remove a user's seat or prevent them from logging in again. To permanently revoke a user's access, disable their account in your identity provider.
seat_management_description: Seats are what the active users in your account consume. Remove a user will revoke their sessions and free up one seat.
session_management_description: Sessions are the event generates when users log in. Revoke sessions will terminate active sessions.
table_description: View your users’ identity, devices, activities and revoke active sessions.
title: Users
user_identity_page_description: View user identity details and the get-identity endpoint for this login session.
user_risk_info: Represents user activity that could introduce risk to your organization.
